      },
      "beast:ofCreature": {
        "@id": "beastiary:creature_centaur"
      },
      "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment": {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "\"Eurytus and the centaurs in Ovid embody teriomorphic chaos as the instigators of the Centauromachia: the bestial appetite triggered by wine erupts into collective violence. The general fall from human rationality into bestial behavior represents also catamorphic descent, the degradation of the hybrid form downward into pure animal impulse."
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "beastiary:genesis_phoenix_claudio",
      "@type": "beast:Genesis",
      "beast:hasGenesisDescription": {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "The Phoenix is not born of parents but self-immolates upon a pyre of aromatic wood at the end of its life cycle to be reborn from its own ashes."
      },
