      "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment": {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "Hesiod places the chimera among the monstrous, shameful offspring of Typhon and Echidna, a primordial and violent chaos-being whose fire-breathing, multi-headed body is teriomorphic terror in its most concentrated, genealogical form."
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "beastiary:citation_beowulf_1",
      "@type": "beast:Citation",
      "beast:extractedFrom": {
        "@id": "beastiary:source_beowulf"
      },
      "beast:hasPassageText": "Then the ancient dusk-scather / The fire-dragon. Found the great treasure standing all open, / He who flaming and fiery flies to the barrows, / Naked war-dragon, nightly escapeth / Encompassed with fire ; men under heaven / Widely beheld him. 'Tis said that he looks for / The hoard in the earth, where old he is guarding / The heathenish treasure ; he'll be nowise the better.",
      "beast:hasSequenceIdentifier": "Chapter XXXIII",
      "beast:isTextualReferenceOf": {
        "@id": "beastiary:int_dragon_beowulf"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "beastiary:citation_aberdeen_1",
      "@type": "beast:Citation",
      "beast:extractedFrom": {
        "@id": "beastiary:source_aberdeen_bestiary"
      },
      "beast:hasPassageText": "The phoenix is a bird of Arabia, so called either because its colouring is Phoenician purple, or because there is only one of its kind in the whole world. It lives for upwards of five hundred years, and when it observes that it has grown old, it erects a funeral pyre for itself from small branches of aromatic plants, and having turned to face the rays of the sun, beating its wings, it deliberately fans the flames for itself and is consumed in the fire. But on the ninth day after that, the bird rises from its own ashes.",
      "beast:hasSequenceIdentifier": "Folio 55r",
      "beast:isTextualReferenceOf": {
        "@id": "beastiary:int_phoenix_aberdeen"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "beastiary:genesis_basilisk_theophilus",
      "@type": "beast:Genesis",
      "beast:hasGenesisDescription": [
        {
          "@language": "en",
          "@value": "Hatched from a yolkless egg laid by an old cock"
        },
        {
          "@language": "en",
          "@value": "incubated by a toad in place of the natural mother."
        }
      ],
